  "name": "Siren with Loudspeaker",
  "lesson": {
    "title": "Siren with Loudspeaker",
    "description": "Two-NPN astable siren on 5V USB with a tact button in series on the supply path — press to run the oscillator, release to stop. A loudspeaker cube on the collector branch; 47µF and 1µF cross-couple the bases with 10kΩ and 47kΩ bias. Compare lessons 94–96 (always-on speaker oscillators) and lesson 60 (tact + single transistor)."
  },
